description: Arden Variations is a theme and variations form in three movements, each replete with melodic, harmonic, and rhythmic variations on the simple 8-measure chorale theme of the opening Prelude. Originally intended as an analytical study for students in the composer's Advanced Harmony course at Louisiana State University, the piece seemed to demand further development as each new harmonic device was introduced. Its

Mark Camphouse weaves beautifully musical strains of the classic folk song in his Fantasia for concert band. This intimate and lyrical setting will challenge and inspire your band while exploring and celebrating our rich folk song heritage. (8:35) This title is available in SmartMusic.
sous_titre: on Black Is the Color of My True Love's Hair

description: Whitewater Journey takes both the performers and audience on an adventurous river-ride over foaming rapids and swiftly flowing currents. Midway through the trip, a gentle respite is encountered where the grandeur of the scenery can be appreciated, but soon the river again demands attention until the final destination is safely reached.

titre: As the Robin to the Meadow

description: Based on the chant Veni Creator Spiritus, Of Times Medieval takes your audience on a journey through Medieval Europe. Your audience will experience an ancient monastery, a celebration in the streets, and a clash of swords and shields. This bold and expressive piece is a must for any program.

For children, Hanukkah brings thoughts of a miracle from long, long ago and excitement each holiday season about what awaits. This new work musically conveys both reflection and joy with colorful scoring and expressive writing. Add wonder to your holiday performance this year with Hanukah Is Here. (2:35)

Take a trip to the Big Easy with "New Orleans Strut." Even very young bands will get into the groove of this piece, and the low brass and woodwinds will enjoy playing the hint of "The Saints" hidden in their parts. This Dixieland Jazz inspired piece is sure to be a favorite with young bands and their audiences alike. Correlates to Accent on Achievement, Book 1, page 19. (2:25) This title is available in SmartMusic.

This delightful band transcription of a Debussy piano classic is an ideal teaching tool. The piece will help teach tempo, dynamics, and rhythms such as the sixteenth-eighth-sixteenth pattern. The perfect selection for your next concert or contest. (2:51)

More Games! is a continuation of the composer's previous work, Games! Different games represented are tag, cloud shapes, and capes and swords. This piece, full of energy and child-like vitality, is sure to inspire your audience's inner-child. Get ready to play More Games!

Since 1919, Once in Royal David's City has been used to commence the worldwide BBC broadcast of the Festival of Nine Lessons and Carols on Christmas Eve from the University of Cambridge in England. Contrasting the pomp of a royal procession with gentler passages, this arrangement is mindful of the quiet eve evoked by the lyrics. Highlights include opening chimes and bells, a marching marcato section, and an ending

Campfire Sketches was inspired by songs of the old west-folk songs that pioneers might have sung while sitting around a campfire. The first movement, All the Pretty Little Horses, is a lullaby that is perfect for teaching legato playing and phrasing. The second movement, Cindy, is an up-tempo number in an old west style that gives all sections a chance to sparkle.

titre: All Is Calm ( based on Silent Night )
Upon The Wings Of The Wind

description: Everyone loves a round, and your audience will too when you put Rockin' a Round on your next concert. John O'Reilly has taken some of the most famous rounds and placed a fun rock-style beat underneath. Your audience's toes will be tapping in no time! Correlated with Yamaha Band Student, Book 1, page 12.

The sounds of ancient Greek soldiers doing battle are heard in this powerful original by John O'Reilly. The piece uses only six notes, yet sounds surprisingly sophisticated. Great fun and a great morale builder for your beginning band. Correlated with Yamaha Band Student, Book 1, page 10.

sous_titre: Bass Section Feature (Featuring: Jingle Bells / Dreydl Song / Jolly Old St. Nicholas)

description: Depicting the thrill of a hot-air balloon ride, Northwest Rising is yet another concert showstopper from Robert Sheldon. From the excitement of the initial liftoff to the quiet calm of floating in air, to the anticipation of the thrill of landing, this piece will take your band and audience on the musical balloon ride of a lifetime. Woodwind glissandi, refreshing harmonies and driving percussion help make Northwest

titre: Overture on an American Folk Tune

description: This energetic concert or festival opener is sure to make your band sparkle! Highlander is full of bright melodies for the woodwinds and trumpets juxtaposed with bagpipe-like drones in the low brass, calling to mind images of old Scotland. Generous use of the piccolo adds to the Scottish flair. A lovely woodwind chorale provides for an interesting contrast in the middle section, only to be interrupted by the exciting

sous_titre: Low Brass / Low Woodwind Section Feature

description: Steve Hodges creates a rhythmically interesting concert selection using nothing more complicated than dotted quarter eighth-note figures - perfect for your developing band! A syncopated low brass figure in 3/4 times serves as the foundation for the soaring melodies and countermelodies. Great for working on both legato and marcato playing, as well as on dynamics, articulations and key changes!

Close your next concert in style with this great patriotic original by Jay Althouse and Sally Albrecht. Scored for band with optional chorus, this arragement features a fresh treatment of American in 4/4 time and will provide a high-impact finale for your next program. Choral parts are available in 2-part, 3-part mixed and SATB voicings. InstruPax includes: director's score, 2 trumpets, alto sax, trombone [opt.
titre: Of Thee I Sing, America! (incorporates America)

description: This is not just another easy march . . . it's a work that provides a wide range of teaching possibilities for your students, including musical style and ensemble playing. This compelling and powerful number features an exciting interchange between the trumpet and percussion sections. Perfect for opening or closing your next elementary concert. Put your music program into orbit with Apollo March!

John Kinyon  has another winner with this transcription of the symphonic masterpiece ' The Moldau .' A tribute to  Smetana 's beloved river, this captivating piece describes the flowing and turmoil ofwater in musical terms. The parts are written well within the capabilities of young performers while keeping the essence of the original. This will add more than a little class to your next concert.

description: The popular "Cortège" from Rimsky-Korsakov's opera Mlada has always been a great favorite in Eric Leidzen's classic band transcription. This engraved edition updates the scoring for the contemporary band and provides it with a complete full score. This transcription belongs in every serious band library. Duration: 4'40"

Dans les années 1960, le groupe Martha Reeves and the Vandellas compte parmi les artistes phares du label Motown avec Marvin Gaye, Smokey Robinson et les Jackson 5. Leur chanson emblématique  Nowhere to Run  a triomphé dans le monde entier tant pour l’histoire d’amour malheureuse qu’elle raconte que pour l'audace des percussions (tambourin et chaînes neige) qui enveloppent la mélodie de leur battement métallique.

Premier voyage, premier tableau : nous découvrons la Place Rouge, le Kremlin et le parc Gorki, célèbre lieu de promenade moscovite. Si la  Marchen° 1  est incontestablement la plus célèbre, la  Marche n° 3 en Ut mineur  est la plus achevée en terme de musicalité et de techniques de composition. Les mouvements de rassemblement remontent aux commencements de l’histoire de l’humanité.Aujourd’hui encore,de nombreux festivals réunissent des centaines, voire des milliers de personnes dans une ambiance de fête et de partage. Cette composition de Johan Nijs est dédié au Général de Brigade Dany Van de Ven, Attaché de Défense,Naval et de l’Air près l’Ambassade de Belgique Washington. Stateside Salute (“Un salut aux États-Unis”) est une composition pleine de swing qui rappelle, entre autres, les sonorités caractéristiques du Big Band américain.

Euphoria is a bracing composition which concentrates its energy on the baritones/euphoniums. The solo parts require at least two soloists. This piece opens with a syncopated introduction followed by a statement of the simple melodic theme interpreted by the baritones/euphoniums. The style of performance is particularly affected by the alternation of staccato and legato passages. The finale of this work develops

Bay Festival depicts a wonderful summer atmosphere that characterises the regions where the sun, the sea and the sand are stars. Take your band on a trip to warmer climates with this exciting work. An ideal piece for any summer concert.

Claribelle is fairly unique as a solo piece as rather than using one soloist it uses the whole clarinet section to play the solo part. . The composition is characterised by a fast tempo and by a theme which primarily consists of scale patterns that create a virtuoso character. Wim Laseroms wrote the piece in ABA-form with the accompaniment in the middle section having a somewhat more lyric character than that of the

Avec Constellation, Bertrand Moren, jeune compositeur suisse, signe une marche lumineuse et éclatante pour Orchestre d’Harmonie. Divisée en deux mouvements - l’un rythmiquement dynamique, l’autre expressif et lyrique - cette marche de concert, très accessible, respire la fraîcheur et la spontanéité.

Ottorino Respighi est le plus connu des compositeurs italiens du XXe siècle. Il doit sa notoriété son triptyque les  Fontaines de Rome , les  Pins de Rome  et les  Fêtes Romaines . Fasciné par la musique ancienne, il s’inspire d’un recueil d’œuvres pour luth des XVIe et XVIIe siècles pour composer les trois suites de  Danses et Airs antiques . In this entertaining march the composer describes the happy atmosphere on a journey to a big party in the forest. Good weather and beautiful surroundings redound in this lively march in 2/4 time.

description: Reminiscencia Gitana was originally a piano piece. André Waignein wrote the piece for the Spanish pianist Blanca Quevedo, a student of his at the Royal Conservatoire of Brussels. This work has all the elements that make a composition interesting: melody, virtuosity and most importantly the ‘Gitana’ (gypsy) character. Each section follows on without interruption making a contrasting whole that will captivate both

La bagatelle est une courte pièce instrumentale au propos modeste, généralement destinée au clavier (clavecin ou piano). André Waignein a composé trois bagatelles pour Orchestre Junior. Ces compositions légères de caractère développent des lignes mélodiques colorées et contrastées, fluides et puissantes, sereines et dynamiques.

Interlude for Band  a été donné en création mondiale en 1987 par l’Orchestre d’Harmonie des Jeunes de Suisse sous la direction de Félix Hauswirth. Cette composition est basée sur un motif mélodique de trois notes et développe une succession de motifs et figures rythmiques. Les bois se distinguent particulièrement par la virtuosité avec laquelle ils exposent les lignes mélodiques.

description: Michael Giacchino's soundtrack for the highly anticipated follow-up to 2009s STAR TREK is dramatic and evocative. Using a mixture of familiar previous themes along with new material, this medley for band brings the excitement and drama of the film to the concert stage.
titre: Highlights From Star Trek Into Darkness

description: Here is very easy arrangement of  One Direction 's popular hit  What Makes You Beautiful . With a driving pulse and catchy melodies, this is sure to be a hit with beginning players.

Here is a powerful symphonic setting of music from the award-winning movie based on the Broadway classic. This medley includes the new song Suddenly, composed for the film, in addition to the familiar melodies Look Down, At the End of the Day, I Dreamed a Dream, Master of the House and Do You Hear the People Sing?
This upbeat hit recorded by Carly Rae Jepsen took the charts by storm and became a pop anthem. This great sounding arrangement will go together quickly and liven up any concert.

Recorded by Pink and Nate Ruess (from the group fun.) this pop anthem has become one of the standout hits from 2013. The tuneful nature and moderate rock style make this particularly appealing to players and audience alike.

description: Composed especially for the film adaptation of Les Misérables and sung by Hugh Jackman (Jean Valjean), this song offers a beautiful and tender moment. Nicely scored for young players, this arrangement will sound full even with thelimited technical demands.

Featuring jazz influenced harmonies and tuneful melodies, the music of Henry Mancini appeals to all generations. This outstanding medley for young players includes the timeless favorites The Pink Panther, Baby Elephant Walk,The Sweetheart Tree, and Peter Gunn.

Composed as a tribute to generations of American servicemen and women buried at Arlington National Cemetery near Washington, D.C., this powerful and emotional work is a fitting addition to any memorial occasion or patrioticconcert. This well-paced tribute features some of his best-known works. Includes:They're Playing My Song, What I Did For Love, The Entertainer, The Way We Were, and One.
From the iTunes hit list to the dance floor, here is a tuneful and upbeat medley of some of the hottest dance hits today. Includes: Moves Like Jagger, Good Time, and Party Rock Anthem.

Written in a traditional French style this stately march draws its title from the famous Arc de Triomphe in Paris. Terrific as a change of pace march, this unique work is solidly scored with fanfare-like figures and appealingmelodies. Dur: 2:00
As the title implies, this dynamic piece for beginners is more about rock than it is science! Your players will enjoy the stomping and clapping and powerful themes. Dur: 1:20 (Grade .5)

Your beginning players will enjoy digging into this unique and somewhat sinister-sounding piece! The percussion play an important role with various metal sounds, and even at this very easy level there is plenty of variety in thescoring. 1:40 (Grade 1)

Designed for second-year players, Michael's energetic overture provides mature and dynamic sounds at a very attainable and easy to learn level. Combining full band unison statements along with some unusual harmonic effects, thisis impressive music for young bands. Dur: 2:45

The P-47 Thunderbolt was one of the workhouse airplanes of World War II, becoming the most produced, and also largest single piston engine fighter plane in history. This dramatic overture for band musically tells the story of thislegendary plane. (The composer's father piloted a P-47 during the war in 1944). The opening heroic strain is contrasted with a slow, reflective middle section before returning to the fast

The sound of chimes and bells can evoke the Christmas spirit in all of us. This sparkling and joyful medley of familiar carols features a distinctive orchestration and style, and is sure to become a holiday favorite. Includes:Westminster Chimes, The Merry Bells All Ring, I Heard the Bells on Christmas Day and Ukrainian Bell Carol.

Here is an impressive-sounding musical snapshot portraying the sights and sounds of this beautiful, artistic and historic city. The opening, metallic Steel City theme reflects its industrial heritage. This section builds to themajestic City of Bridges theme representing the grandeur of the surrounding rivers and 446 bridges. These themes develop and intertwine becoming the driving, urban City of Champions section

The Native American Omaha Tribe believed in an inseparable union between earth and sky. Commissioned for the Nebraska All-State 8th Grade Band, Michael Sweeneys Earth and Sky celebrates this ideal with a balance ofwoodwind motifs and delicate textures (sky) contrasted with an underlying percussion ostinato and feature spots (earth). Rich chordal accompaniments and soaring melodies provide continuity and flow in this
Phillip Phillips 's  Home  for Concert Band. Full score. Grade 1 1/2.

In boxing, the term seconds out refers to the moment when coaches and trainers (or seconds) must be out of the ring, leaving the competitors alone to face the competition. In a similar vein, this composition provides a musicaldescription of the challenges and triumphs of students as they transition from middle to high school, leaving their seconds (parents, mentors, etc.) behind to face life on their own terms.

Winning Grammy and Emmy awards for Henry Mancini, this timeless TV theme has come to epitomize “spy” music. This unique arrangement for concert band features an optional solo section where any number of players canimprovise over the simple chord structure or play the sample written solos that are provided.

Le grand succès de la superstar américaine Katy Perry est enfin disponible pour orchestre d’harmonie. Une ambiance soft-rock et une mélodie particulièrement puissante combleront de joie vos jeunes musiciens et l’ensemble de vosauditeurs. Roar !!!

Il est fort à parier que la sautillante chanson  Gangnam Style  fera vibrer vos musiciens et auditeurs. Son humour et son rythme accrocheur sont tout autant présents dans la version de Robert Longfield. Il ne vous reste plus qu’àrajouter la chorégraphie, si vous le souhaitez !

Welcome to the Jungle , oeuvre incontournable du groupe Guns N’ Roses, a marquée de part sa mélodie accessible à tous et son rythme endiablé, non seulement tous les amateurs de Hard-Rock mais également tout le grand public. Dansl’arrangement de Paul Murtha, les saxophones auront la possibilité d’interpréter la voix soliste et les cuivres celle de jouer les riffs caractéristiques dans un

Le compositeur Alan Silvestri a écrit les plus belles musiques du cinéma récent. Avec  A Night at the Movies , un arrangement signé Michael Brown, nous assistons à la projection de  The Avengers, The Polar Express, Night at the Museum,Forrest Gump  et  Back to the Future .
titre: Alan Silvestri: A Night at the Movies

description: Michael Jackson a laissé un héritage de succès pop irrésistibles, et  Bad  en fait certainement partie. Habilement arrangé par Johnnie Vinson pour une interprétation très facile, cette pièce sera populaire auprès des élèves comme de leursparents.

Cette pièce pour musiciens débutants s’ouvre avec une fanfare majestueuse précédant une marche mélodique. Malgré la facilité de ce morceau, Michael Oare y a introduit suffisamment de variété et de contrastes pour satisfaire et motiver tous lesmembres de l’orchestre.

Idéal pour tout événement lié aux États-Unis ou simplement pour apporter de la variété un concert, voici un arrangement enjoué et créatif d’airs bien connus outre-Atlantique. Stephen Bulla débute avec  You’re a Grand Old Flag , auquel faitsuite le trio « hurrah for the flag of the free » de  Stars and Stripes Forever , et termine avec une version enlevée de  Yankee Doodle Boy . De la gaîté en perspective !

L’effet créé par la  Cup Song  extraite du film  Pitch Perfect  (The Hits Girls) avec Anna Kendrick dans le rôle principal, a engendré beaucoup d’imitations. Avec cet arrangement, offrez à votre pupitre de percussionnistes(ou à d’autres membres de l’orchestre) de se placer sous les feux de la rampe en interprétant la très originale  Cup Song  (chanson de gobelet) et surprenez

Les téléspectateurs de plus de 100 pays ont été enthousiasmés Logo Editio Musica Budapest par la musique de la série télévisée d‘animation  A Kockásfülu Nyúl  (Le lapin aux oreilles carreaux), composée par Árpád Balázs. Le compositeur a choisilui-même les plus belles mélodies de cette suite en sept mouvements, dont chacun représente un personnage de la série.  Music With Chequered Ears  se décline en une version

Over the past five decades music from the James Bond film franchise has become a part of our musical culture. This powerful setting of familiar film themes will appeal to all audiences. Includes: James Bond Theme, Goldfinger,Nobody Does It Better, Skyfall and Live and Let Die.

Il est rare que le titre d’une chanson décrive aussi bien sa musique ! Le méga-succès de Pharrell Williams avait été enregistré pour le film  Despicable Me 2  (Moi, moche et méchant 2), mais il connaît une deuxième vie sur internet, classé parmiles meilleurs titres du palmarès. Il suffit de l’entendre pour se sentir bien !

titre: At the Movies with Hans Zimmer

sous_titre: As performed by Mason Williams and Tommy Emmanuel
As performed by The Rolling Stones
Based on Favorite Sea and River Songs

titre: To a Wild Rose (from Woodland Sketches, Op. 51)

description: Downtown Divertimento  s’inspire des promenades quotidiennes que Johan de Meij fait travers Chelsea, un quartier de Lower Manhattan, New York. Sa journée commence par une balade tranquille dans le parc de Madison Square avec sa chienne,Alice. Ils passent par l’aire d’exercice pour chiens, où elle rencontre d’autres toutous urbains. Sur le chemin du retour, ils font une petite pause pour contempler le Flatiron, un

l‘origine composée pour un spectacle musical et thé tral, cette pièce en reprend le thème et le décline en trois manières différentes comme s’il s’agissait de cartes postales expédiées d’Orient. Une fanfare majestueuse et noble symbolisant lagrandeur des pyramides et la puissance des pharaons - une sorte de danse où la percussion joue un rôle important - une ligne joyeuse et légère vous invitant monter bord du

Cette œuvre fut écrite pour marquer le 375e anniversaire de l’Harmonie Symphonique de Landeck (Autriche) fondée en 1637. Partez en voyage avec vos musiciens et votre public car  Via Claudia  vous emmènera travers les Alpes par un petit matinbrumeux. Formant un cortège imposant, les voyageurs grimpent des pentes ardues, parcourent des pistes accidentées et franchissent des cols abrupts. Lorsqu’ils arrivent au point le
sous_titre: An Imaginary Journey across the Alps

description: Les multiples facettes de la musique africaine ne pourraient se réduire en une seule définition. Elles ont donné naissance de nombreux styles et courants musicaux. Avec  African Beat , André Waignein évoque un rythme africain omniprésent etune sorte de ligne afro-pop résumant quelques mouvements musicaux du continent noir. Invitez votre public participer cet extraordinaire safari musical !

Cette chanson est l’une des plus appréciée du dessin animé  La Reine des neiges . Cet excellent arrangement pour jeunes musiciens est facile apprendre, et conserve toute l’atmosphère et le charme de la chanson originale.
titre: Do You Want to Build a Snowman?

description: De l’énergie, une envie irrépressible de danser et une ligne de basse pleine pression forment la combinaison idéale de cette oeuvre “pumpante” ! La captivante mélodie et les rythmes impétueux se chargent du reste, savoir, faire de  Pump It Up!  une oeuvre dynamique et plaisante rassemblant les très grands succès de Jacob de Haan :  Cornfield Rock, Queen’s Park Melody  et  Discoduction . Lorsque les souvenirs se font

Cette version de  Festival Fanfare for Christmas , l’origine écrite pour orchestre symphonique, s’adresse aux harmonies de niveau avancé. Enregistrée par le Dallas Wind Symphony sous la direction de Jerry Junkin, cette oeuvre magnifique estparfaite pour les fêtes de fin d’année. Débutant avec une fanfare éclatante réservée aux cuivres, la pièce se développe pour inclure l’orchestre entier avec, entre autres, les
titre: Festival Fanfare for Christmas (for Wind Band)

description: Enregistrée en 1989 par Michael W. Smith sur son album dédié aux chants de Noël, cette mélodie inspire paix et quiétude. Donnez du contraste votre programme de concert avec ce moment de pur recueillement.

Représentant musicalement la vitesse et les émotions des skieurs alpins lors d’un exigeant super-G,  Alpine Adventure  est écrite sur un seul tempo rapide et emporte l’auditeur travers une variété de climats stylistiques. Le début et laconclusion de l’oeuvre se distinguent par un style en syncopes énergiques, tandis que le passage central est fondé sur une mélodie plus lyrique en 3/4, mais dont le rythme est tout

L’interprétation d’une pièce somptueuse pour musiciens de tous niveaux procure la motivation nécessaire aux jeunes musiciens.  Shorewood Overture  est destinée être interprétée par des orchestres de divers niveaux. Contrairement aux morceauxtypiquement attribués aux Grands Ensembles, où tout le monde joue la même chose, cette pièce ingénieuse permet chaque niveau de s’exprimer brièvement seul, entre les passages où

Écrite l’origine pour le clavecin, la  Passacaglia  de la suite n° 7 en Sol mineur de Hændel consiste en une série de variations accompagnées d’une progression harmonique de quatre mesures qui se répète. Dans cette transcription magistrale deRobert Longfield, cette merveille baroque met en valeur les couleurs et les timbres de l’orchestre d’harmonie contemporain.

Cette composition inhabituelle dépeint la transformation d’un solide en liquide, puis en gaz. Un thème unique paraît d’abord dense et rigide, puis adopte une qualité lyrique dans le passage central avant de se dissoudre en minusculesfragments dans un finale turbulent.

Robert Longfield a rassemblé trois pièces datant de la Guerre civile américaine dans cet agréable pot-pourri évoquant cette période : l’appel du clairon « Taps », la ballade  Tenting on the Old Campground  et le négro-spiritual  Free atLast .

Enregistré par le groupe American Authors, ce succès pop a déj connu une grande popularité la télévision et autres média, et s’est bien placé au hit-parade. L’ambiance tonique et contagieuse de ce titre est parfaitement adaptée aux orchestresd’harmonie dans cet arrangement robuste de James Kazik.
Arrangé par le légendaire Luther Henderson et récemment enregistré par le Canadian Brass sur le CD  Christmas Time Is Here , cette joyeuse version a été richement adaptée pour orchestre d´harmonie.

Combinant habilement  Jingle Bells  et  God Rest Ye Merry, Gentlemen , cet arrangement charmant pour jeunes musiciens fait penser une promenade en traîneau. Cette musique gaie et entraînante évoque parfaitement la période de Noël.

As One Listens to the Rain is a marriage of two distinct musical ideas. The first, a solitary, solemn melody, is introduced in the trumpet and cloaked in an aura of slowly shifting transparent harmonies. This idea soon gives wayto flowing lines and falling gestures that invoke an image of cascading rainfall. A hymn-like interlude provides a brief respite before the return of the rain which, in this final form, spins
titre: As One Listens to the Rain

description: Continuing in the tradition of her innovative electroacoustic band works including Paper Cut, Immersion, and Tight Squeeze, Alex Shapiro's Liquid Compass takes the musicians and the audience on a journey that spans the mysticaland the triumphant. A subliminal connection to the sea is conveyed through the creative use of metal bowls filled with water, and flutists will particularly enjoy the otherworldly ooh-wah

Les trois mouvements de cette suite représentent trois jouets mécaniques créés au XVIe siècle : un soldat qui marche, une dame qui cueille des fleurs en se baissant et se relevant, et un cheval volant qui trottine en agitant ses ailes. Une pièceespiègle et charmante !

S’inspirant de livres et de films d’aventures imaginaires, cette suite en trois mouvements explore une variété d’ambiances et de styles descriptifs. Le premier mouvement ( Wizards  Magiciens) est de nature noble et majestueuse, tandis que ledeuxième ( Elves  Lutins) est plus enjoué et espiègle. Le dernier mouvement ( Talking Animals  Animaux parlants) combine énergie rythmique et plusieurs tempos pour créer un climat

Dans  Villages , votre orchestre sera divisé en petites communautés bien distinctes qui vont être invitées communiquer les unes avec les autres par différentes lignes mélodiques et fragments rythmiques. Une manière très originale de rappelerque la communication peut également s’installer gr ce ce bel art que nous pratiquons... la Musique !

Composed as a tribute to legendary thoroughbred racehorse/2006 Kentucky Derby winner Barbaro, this work for mature ensembles captures the excitement and pageantry of race day at the track. Rhythmically dynamic from start tofinish, this is a perfect opener for festival or concert use. Dur: 2:05
titre: Fanfare and Call to the Post

description: Ancient Desert Drone  was composed for Orchestra in 1940 at the request of Percy Grainger, who encouraged the idea of using a single pitch drone throughout the work (similar to Grainger's own  The ImmovableDo ) and to whom the piece is dedicated. While the work suggests an Eastern charm with its distinctive mode and primitive rhythms, Cowell himself stated there was no particular programmatic intent. This

Hungarian-style dance music which flourished in the 16th and 17th centuries - generally referred to as ungaresca - represents a valuable part of European musical tradition. István Győrffy's work (2007-2010) is a late successor of this tradition. It was written with the intention of embodying the eastern-central European tradition in order to present an alternative to the current fashions of music for wind

Homecoming is a distinctly American piece of music which ventures emotionally from doubt, to hope, and finally to celebration. The most simple wind instrument of all, the human voice, echoes meaningful homecomings, wherever home may be and from whatever circumstance one returns. Written for the soldiers of the U.S. Army TRADOC Band, Homecoming seamlessly flows between traditional styles that originated in the U.S.,

Rarely does a blockbuster movie include a soundtrack that becomes such an important element of the film itself. With songs from character Peter Quill's “Awesome Mix” here is a dynamic medley for band that features the  Marvel Studios Fanfare, Hooked on a Feeling, Come and Get Your Love, Groot Cocoon  (lyric theme from the score),  Cherry Bomb , and  Ain't No Mountain High Enough .
titre: Soundtrack Highlights from Guardians of the Galaxy

description: “Sparkling Diamonds” are one of many famous songs performed in the movie “Moulin Rouge” (2001) and consist of the two tunes “Diamonds Are a Girls Best Friend” with elements of the Madonna hit “Material Girl”.“Diamonds Are a Girls Best Friend was written as early as 1949 and are performed by several great artists. Among them are Marilyn Monroe who was the first to make it a big hit. Nicole Kidman perform the song in

Paru pour la première fois en 1986,  Livin’ On a Prayer  est devenu l’indicatif musical du groupe rock Bon Jovi. Gr ce son emploi constant en culture pop, des évènements sportifs ou dans des jeux vidéo ce classique du rock reste toujours aussi populaire. Voici un arrangement frappant pour les salles de concert !

Three Washington Statues  fut commandé par la United States Army Band « Pershing’s Own », dirigée par le Colonel Thomas H. Palmatier. Certains des monuments, mémoriaux et statues les plus emblématiques du monde se trouvent Washington D.C.Philip Sparke en a choisi trois comme inspiration pour ce morceau : « The Lincoln Memorial » où le compositeur dépeint la grandeur de ce temple grec de style dorique ; « The Martin
A playable and fun march with exiting challenges for the players. Lyric lines in woodwinds to powerful passages in low brass. We salute all bands!
This march is written for the 70-year anniversary of the conclusion of the World War II in 1945.

Using only limited rhythms and ranges, Bandroom Rock is a great way to get your beginning players energized and motivated. The low brass starts things off, following the rest of the band and short feature spots for the percussion section. Fun for all!

Featuring a bright dance tempo and catchy melodies, this arrangement of Meghan Trainor's pop hit is easy to learn and fun to play. Horns and saxes take the lead in the beginning, but the low brass and trumpets get into the act aswell.

Originally composed for the acclaimed U.S. Army Band Herald Trumpets, Paul Murtha's dramatic fanfare pays tribute to the heroic men and women of the New York City Fire Department who lost their lives in 2001. Dur: 1:00

Propelled throughout by a constant driving pulse, Michael Oare's exciting work pits opposing elements of harmony and rhythm against each other, portraying a sense of musical equilibrium. Creative interplay between winds andpercussion, along with shifting meters and changing textures, adds to the effectiveness of this unique piece commissioned by the U.S Navy Band for their performance at the 2014 Midwest Clinic in

Taking inspiration from the lakes of northern New York state, as well as Niagara Falls, Falling Water is composed in the form of a fantasia, featuring multiple sections of varied textures, restless tonality, and dramatic energy.Breaking free from some of the usual conventions of traditional concert band writing, this work is fresh sounding and a welcome addition to the repertoire for young bands. Dur: 4:45

James Newton Howard composed this dynamic fanfare for the closing segment of the 1993 movie Grand Canyon (starring Danny Glover, Kevin Kline and Steve Martin). The film is now largely forgotten, however the music remains a vibrantand powerful statement and a very effective concert opener. Skillfully adapted by Paul Murtha with heroic brass figures, woodwind flourishes, and thundering percussion.

Commissioned by the Richardson (TX) Community Band, Silver Celebration commemorates 25 years of service by their conductor, George Jones. The work combines elements of traditional march style with the bravura of epic film scores,resulting in a piece that is both festive and celebratory in nature. The opening is a rousing 6/8 march featuring various sections of the band and exciting cross rhythms, and then contrasted

This beautiful and sensitive composition was written to celebrate the beginning of UNITED SOUND, an organization whose purpose is to put instruments into the hands of special needs students. The beginning section features optional solo opportunities for flute, alto sax and trumpet. From there the piece adds layers of sonorities as the full ensemble builds to the emotional and powerful final strains.

This lyric work provides an opportunity for your band to experience the musical style of Chopin in an effective setting for second year players. Featuring legato phrases, darker sonorities, and an engaging harmonic progression,Poem Romantic No. 1 offers musical rewards for the young level. Dur: 2:40

Drawing inspiration from American poet Maya Angelou's inspirational poem On the Pulse of Morning, this unique work for band offers challenges and rewards for young players. Using the imagery of a rock, a river, a tree, Angelouchallenges us all to work for unity and peace. The music ranges from an energetic percussive pulse (rock) that utilizes plastic buckets played throughout the ensemble, to a flowing chorale theme

Based on the legendary lake creature that lives in Okanagan Lake in Canada, Ogopogo uses quirky orchestration and rhythms to bring the monster to life. The enormous creature rises from the depths, plays in the waves and thensuddenly disappears back into the darkness. Ideal for a unique change of pace, Ogopogo uses the first 6 notes of the B-flat scale and is written in the Phrygian mode.

In Celtic folklore, a selkie is a mythical creature appearing as a seal in water, but taking human form on land. In this striking setting for second-year players the first movement, in a lyric and melancholy style, portrays theselkie as a baby seal. The second movement depicts a young boy on land and employs a number of characteristics of traditional Scottish folk tunes. This marvelous work provides opportunities for

Imagine a band far off in the distance marching toward you - soft at first, the music becomes louder and louder: the red capes of the band sway in the wind, getting closer and closer. It was this image that inspired Flying Colors.Famed bandmaster Arthur Delamont always programmed a march in his concerts, and the hallmark of his band was their red capes. The work begins very softly with a distant snare drum beat. The
sous_titre: Third Movement of A Tribute to Arthur Delamont

description: Celebrating its 130th anniversary, the Woodstock City Band of Woodstock, Illinois (at one time known as Spring City) commissioned this dynamic overture honoring the long-standing tradition of summer concerts in the historic townsquare. Joyous and celebratory in nature, Spring City Overture features a dramatic opening segment that builds to the tuneful main theme. A brief reflective lyric section provides a moment of

Inspired by the mysterious stone formations of Stonehenge, Ancient Stone Circles creates an atmosphere of ancient times using modal melodies, rich scoring and exotic percussion. You'll hear the huge stones being transported,follow a Druid procession, and feel the awe and wonderment of this mystical place. Dur: 2:15

Famed bandmaster Arthur Delamont always started his concerts with a rousing overture, and Front and Center is in this proud tradition. In a non-stop 9/8 rhythm, this piece explodes with energy and effervescence. Full of powerfulfanfares, lively melodies, driving percussion and dynamic contrasts, this exciting concert opener moves through different musical colors without ever losing its relentless drive. An
sous_titre: First Movement of A Tribute to Arthur Delamont

description: This is the title-track of the third studio-album by the Northern-Ireland singer and saxophonist Van Morrison. Both the song alone and the record album are among the artists biggest successes. The album is covering many musical genres.Moondance is representing the jazz-side of these. The style is a mid-temo, swing-feel typical for numerous jazz-tunes. This arrangement have solo options for altosax and/or trumpet.

An American Tapestry is a continuous medley of three American folk songs: the happy-go-lucky The Girl I Left Behind Me, the somber and reflective He's Gone Away, and the foot-stompin' hoedown Ol' Dan Tucker. The setting was originally composed for chamber winds (11 players) and has been completely re-scored by the composer in this new edition for full wind ensemble. The contrasting tempi and sentiments of the tunes,
sous_titre: A setting of three American folk songs

description: Images of Bellac  se repose sur une série d’images du village pittoresque de Bellac dans le Limousin en France. L’œuvre représente plusieurs scènes et vues du village par des thèmes merveilleux ainsi que des séquences rythmiques qui symbolisent la disposition positive et dynamique des habitants. Ce morceau se prête des concerts ou des concours.

Nie Vergessen  (« je ne t’oublierai jamais ») était un grand succès du duo électro-pop Glasperlenspiel. Tiré de leur deuxième album  Grenzenlos  (« sans limites »), cette chanson établit une nouvelle norme dans ce genre.
From the blockbuster film and latest adventures of the Avengers, Danny Elfman has created a suitably powerful and dramatic soundtrack. Here is the main theme ready to explode onto the concert stage!

Around the Globe  est une suite simple pour orchestre ou ensemble de jeunes. Cette œuvre écrite pour instrumentation flexible augmente en difficulté. On voyage travers les Etats-Unis, l’Allemagne et la République Tchèque sur ce trajet avant de finir en Angleterre avec  Rule Britannia , bien s r !

When you look out at the ocean, what does it resemble? This unique, driving composition paints that picture. The upper Atlantic beaches hold many stories, from beautifully scenic sunrises to the wrath of Hurricane Sandy. Threehigh schools in Toms River, New Jersey commissioned the musical depiction of their celebrated shore, from joy to turbulence. The heavy emphasis on percussion only adds to the exciting build and

With its Latin title translated as onward and upward this brief yet energetic overture for second-year players captures the spirit of adventure found in Henry Wadsworth Longfellow's 1841 poem of the same name. The energetic pulseand powerful melodies will engage the imagination of your young players. Dur: 2:20

The haunting melody of this traditional tune likely dates to the Middle Ages, and was published by British composer Ralph Vaughan Williams in the 1906 English Hymnal. Freely adapted by Johnnie Vinson in this setting for youngbands, the minor melody is stated first by low clarinets and horns. The next section introduces an original theme, which is then combined with the first melody in the moving final section.

Ce tube de pop enregistré par Mariah Carey en 1994 reste toujours un favori de Noël. Commençant par un tempo modéré et une introduction lyrique, cet arrangement efficace pour de jeunes orchestres passe ensuite un style de swing rythmé avec des orchestrations et dynamiques variées.
titre: All I Want for Christmas Is You

description: With the hint of a tropical paradise plus a catchy melody, this familiar holiday tune has been recorded by countless artists and was featured in the hit movie Elf. This solidly scored version for band is sure to bring a smile andwill sound great with limited rehearsal time.

Commissioned by Furman University for the inauguration of its 12th president, Jay Bocook's Gloriana is based on The Faerie Queene, an incomplete English epic poem written by Edmund Spenser and dedicated to Queen Elizabeth I. Inthe poem, Queen Elizabeth is represented as the faerie queene herself, Gloriana. This stately work for winds and percussion has a regal quality enhanced by soaring melodies and punctuated with

The word svimeslått, which is the title of this piece in Norwegian, has two meanings. One meaning is ”knocked out”, whilst the other, ”slått”, means a folk melody/dance.Svimeslått is one of several folk dances, all of them with humorous titles, originally written by Øystein Olsen Vadsten. Norwegian culture is the basis for these dances, both rhythmically and melodically. The accompaniment has brought this funpiece

You’ll find many kinds of super heroes around you. This is a suite presenting the super heroes of the band: 1. Low Brass Man 2. The Flute Phantom 3. Trumpet Lady 4. Sgt. Major Minor  The short movements can beplayed individually or together as I suite.
titre: The Super Heroes of the Band

description: Originally written for the zany and outrageous Blake Edwards comedy The Great Race, this beautifully melodic ballad became a popular and endearing song on its own. Nicely arranged here for young bands by Robert Longfield.
titre: The Sweetheart Tree (from The Great Race)
And All The Bells On Earth Shall Ring

description: Capture your beginning bands imagination with this aggressive concert opener using only the first six notes introduced in most band methods. Each part is written with melodic interest. Memorable themes, changing textures and contrasting styles make this an outstanding teaching piece suitable for concert and festival use. A superb addition to the beginning band repertoire!

Opening on Broadway in 1951, and garnering multiple awards for the 2015 revival, few musicals can boast as many lasting and memorable songs as this Rodgers and Hammerstein masterpiece. Drawing on the classic orchestrations by Robert Russell Bennett, here is a fabulous medley for the symphonic stage. Includes: 'Something Wonderful', 'I Whistle a Happy Tune', 'I Have Dreamed', 'The March of the Siamese Children',
titre: Symphonic Highlights from The King and I

description: Fans of the popular and long-standing BBC television series  Doctor Who  will immediately recognize this powerful theme as the heroic music of the Eleventh Doctor (Matt Smith). Of the many fabulous musical themes from the series, this remains one of the most popular and dramatic.
titre: I Am the Doctor (from Doctor Who)

description: Sung by the Jets gang in  Leonard Bernstein 's  West Side Story , this familiar song is filled with energy and rambunctious humor. With the melodic phrases being bounced from section to section, this clever adaptation by  Paul Murtha  is a great way to liven up the concert stage.
titre: Gee, Officer Krupke - From West Side Story

description: This chart features the sound of a New Orleans funeral marching band historically known as the "Second Line" which follows behind the family and casket. It’s a time for celebration coming after the initial mourning period. Lots of fun to play in the style of a funky, marching Dixieland band. The harmonic form is the Blues and there is room made for soloing both inside the ensemble and for featured soloists. Includes

In this exciting fanfare, the brass and woodwinds proclaim majestic excitement through the use of interesting harmonies and crisp rhythmic motion. Aggressive percussion writing adds to the intensity of the performance. Written for the very youngest ensembles, "Blazon!" is the perfect selection to open your next concert.

Edgy and rhythmic, this explosive work will excite your students and audiences! Thick harmonies and gritty percussion writing give the impression of playing inside a noisy factory. Powerful and energetic, this will be an unforgettable hit at your next festival or concert performance! A brilliant and unique work!

This lively Hungarian folk dance, originally set for solo violin and piano by Italian composer Vittorio Monti, has been arranged for solo instrument and concert band for the Barnhouse "Spotlight" series by Andrew Glover. This rhapsodical work allows the soloist to display great lyrical skills as well as technical virtuosity!
